    <title>Roots of Bernstein-Sato polynomials for monomial ideals: a positive
  characteristic approach</title>
    <summary>  We describe the roots of the Bernstein-Sato polynomial of a monomial ideal
using reduction mod p and invariants of singularities in positive
chracteristic. We give in this setting a positive answer to a problem of
Takagi, Watanabe and the second author, concerning the dependence on the
characteristic for these invariants of singularities.
</summary>
